The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at a meeting with America's governors. Pence thanked the governors for their service and collaboration in working on issues such as jobs, energy, and combating opiate abuse. He highlighted the progress made in the past year, including 2.5 million new jobs and a 17-year low in unemployment. Pence also emphasized the administration's commitment to ensuring the safety and security of children and schools, particularly in the wake of the recent school shooting in Parkland, Florida. He invited the governors to share their ideas for reform at the federal level and assured them that President Donald Trump is listening and committed to making a difference. The article concludes with Pence introducing President Trump.